## 📋 Features

- ✅ Manage **suspects, victims, witnesses, evidence, and FIR records**
- ✅ Full **CRUD operations** (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
- ✅ **6 relational MySQL tables** with 3NF normalized schema
- ✅ **15+ optimized SQL queries** with JOINs and indexed lookups
- ✅ Structured data handling via **JDBC connectivity**

---

## 🗄️ Database Schema

```
suspects      → id, name, age, crime_type, status
victims       → id, name, age, case_id
witnesses     → id, name, statement, case_id
evidence      → id, description, case_id, collected_date
fir_records   → id, fir_number, date, officer_id, suspect_id
officers      → id, name, badge_number, rank
```

---

## 🚀 How to Run

```bash
# 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/Thanusha2520/police-crime-record-system.git

# 2. Open in your IDE (Eclipse / IntelliJ)

# 3. Import the SQL schema
mysql -u root -p < schema.sql

# 4. Update DB credentials in DBConnection.java
String url = "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/crime_db";
String user = "root";
String password = "your_password";

# 5. Run Main.java
```

